    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've update [your example](https://0x1zjk06k0.codesandbox.io/) to print the text rather than the DOM element. You can see that the text is printed before the alert is shown (use the example outside of CodeSandbox to see the difference). The UI is not updated yet but the DOM is up to date. The `alert` block the UI of the browser, the render of the page included. It should be safe to use the `render` event to perform operations since the DOM is already updated.",
